# Definition

<div class="block">

![Unit Hyperbola](/img/graphs/calculus/unit-hyperbola.png)

Hyperbolic functions are analogs of the trigonometric ones: just as the points $(\cos{t}, \sin{t})$ form a circle with a 
unit radius, the points $(\cosh{t}, \sinh{t})$ form the right half of the equilateral hyperbola.

- *Hyperbolic Sine:* $$ \sinh{x} = \frac{e^x - e^{-x}}{2}. $$
- *Hyperbolic Cosine:* $$ \cosh{x} = \frac{e^x+e^{-x}}{2}. $$
- *Hyperbolic Tangent:* $$ \tanh{x} = \frac{\sinh{x}}{\cosh{x}}. $$

